To write the body of a global procedure using the Script Editor, you use the procedure statement. Here's an example:
```
PROCEDURE procedure_name(parameters)
    // Procedure body with instructions to be executed
end PROCEDURE;
```

Declaring a local 4GL procedure in OpenROAD is also a two-step process. First, you declare the procedure directly in the frame, field, or procedure script. Here's an example:
```
DECLARE PROCEDURE procedure_name(parameters);
    // Procedure body with instructions to be executed
END PROCEDURE;
```
